---
title: Garden Spinach Ricotta Ravioli Dinner’s Just 15 Minutes Away!
description: Tender ravioli are pretty much good in any form, but they’re especially great when packed with fresh spinach and pillowy ricotta. This rendition is “dragged through the garden,” majorly amping up the veggie factor. Yep, this delicious dish is loaded with chopped and ribboned zucchini, diced tomato, and a bevvy of Italian herbs and spices. It’s taken to the next level with a creamy lemon sauce, nutty Parmesan, and a sprinkle of scallion greens. Be still, our pasta-loving hearts…
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/garden-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-75785542.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/garden-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-5e503da9c269401f3266acae-0a0dd33d.pdf
cuisine: Italian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/garden-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-5e503da9c269401f3266acae
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 21 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1160 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 15 minutes
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim ends from @zucchini{1}(shaved into thin ribbons); shave zucchini lengthwise into
thin ribbons using a #peeler{}, rotating as you go. Stop once you get to the
seedy core; finely chop core. Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(whites separated from greens). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Zest 1 lemon and quarter both.

Once water is boiling, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%oz} to
#pot{}. Immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente and floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

> TIP: Gently shake strainer with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as
> possible.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chopped zucchini, tomato, scallion whites, and @Italian seasoning{1%tsp};
cook until veggies are just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Reduce heat under pan with veggies to medium; stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1},
a squeeze of lemon juice, and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water. Reduce heat
to low and cook ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @sour cream{4%tbsp} and
@butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

> 4 SERVINGS: Stir in 1/3 cup reserved pasta cooking water. Use 2 TBSP butter.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Separate zucchini ribbons with your hands, then stir into pan with sauce.

Carefully stir in ravioli. Simmer until sauce is thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Season with salt, pepper, and lemon zest to taste.

Divide ravioli mixture between #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and
@Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.